      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SASSY SPICE (5) has a strong record this track and trip with two wins and three placings from six starts. In the money last time at Shepparton (25.75) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 1.75 lengths third. Looks well placed and should feature. PAW XENA (2) could manage only second at this track last time but caught the eye when posting a superb 25.17 over 450m at Shepparton the start prior. Top win two back and can measure up again. KING MATTEO (3) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 390m at Shepparton, taking a Mix 3/4 in a dazzling 21.88. Has the ability and looks a key chance. SPICY ASSASSIN (4) was in the money last start and poses a threat again.",
